# meta-training
===============

This layer provided examples and documents for training purposes.
The main branch is for keeping traing labs and eamples build 
and preped for the next class or yocot/OE summits.

The branching will align with a Summit or training slot.

Prep
================

Many of the examples with run QEMU. One method is via slirp. Please configure
your local account ssh in the following:

vi ~/.ssh/config

Host qemu
    User root
    Hostname localhost
    Port 2222
    StrictHostKeyChecking no
    UserKnownHostsFile /dev/null

then is just a matter of running qemu like:

runqemu <machine> slirp <extra options>


Maintenance
================

Send pull requests, patches, comments or questions to yocto@lists.yoctoproject.org

tmp Maintainer: Armin Kuster <akuster808@gmail.com 

When sending single patches, please using something like:
$ git send-email -1 -M --to yocto@lists.yoctoproject.org --subject-prefix='meta-training][PATCH'


